  "subject": "Fix drools-apps CSIT",
  "commit_message": "Fix drools-apps CSIT\n\nNow that the event services is created as an object within drools\nworking memory, the fact count used in the CSIT health check is\nincorrect.  Modified the CSIT to simply look for the existence of\nusecases field.\nAlso fixed warnings about deprecated robot methods.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-3260\nChange-Id: Iec73289f47d4bc2e5774e2de0a79f97be1c31cc8\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\n",
